   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Importando as Bibliotecas"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import qiskit_nature\n",
    "from qiskit_algorithms.optimizers import *\n",
    "from qiskit_nature.units import DistanceUnit\n",
    "from qiskit_nature.second_q.drivers import PySCFDriver\n",
    "from qiskit_algorithms.minimum_eigensolvers import NumPyMinimumEigensolver\n",
    "from qiskit_nature.second_q.algorithms import GroundStateEigensolver\n",
    "from qiskit_nature.second_q.mappers import JordanWignerMapper\n",
    "from qiskit_nature.second_q import *\n",
    "from qiskit_algorithms.minimum_eigensolvers import VQE\n",
    "from qiskit_algorithms.optimizers import SLSQP\n",
    "from qiskit.primitives import Estimator\n",
    "from qiskit_nature.second_q.circuit.library import HartreeFock, UCCSD\n",
    "from qiskit_aer.primitives import Estimator as AerEstimator\n",
    "from qiskit_aer.noise import NoiseModel\n",
    "from qiskit_nature.exceptions import QiskitNatureError\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import time"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Vamos criar algumas funções para facilitação."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "def GS_classic(d, base = \"sto3g\") :\n",
    "\n",
    "    driver = PySCFDriver(\n",
    "        atom= f\"H 0 0 0; H 0 0 {d}\",\n",
    "        basis=base,\n",
    "        charge=0,\n",
    "        spin=0,\n",
    "        unit=DistanceUnit.ANGSTROM,\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    solver = GroundStateEigensolver(\n",
    "        JordanWignerMapper(),\n",
    "        NumPyMinimumEigensolver(),\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    problem = driver.run()\n",
    "    result = solver.solve(problem)\n",
    "\n",
    "    return result.groundenergy + result.nuclear_repulsion_energy"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "intervalo = np.concatenate((np.linspace(0.3,2.5,15), np.linspace(2.5,10,5)))\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "[<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x7f17588ba0e0>]"
      ]

     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"

    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "gs = [GS_classic(a) - GS_classic(20) for a in intervalo]\n",
    "plt.plot(intervalo, gs, '-o')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Agora vamos focar em aplicar POO e usar outros sistemas como a solução por VQE"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def GS_VQE(a, base = 'sto3g', mapper = JordanWignerMapper(), otimizador = COBYLA()):\n",
    "    #Usando Jordan Wigner, vou tentar outros.\n",
    "\n",
    "    #procedimento padrão\n",
    "    driver = PySCFDriver(\n",
    "        atom= f\"H 0 0 0; H 0 0 {a}\",\n",
    "        basis=base,\n",
    "        charge=0,\n",
    "        spin=0,\n",
    "        unit=DistanceUnit.ANGSTROM,\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    es_problem = driver.run()\n",
    "\n",
    "    #Relevante testar outros tipos de Ansatz e o uso de hartreefock\n",
    "    ansatz = UCCSD(\n",
    "        es_problem.num_spatial_orbitals,\n",
    "        es_problem.num_particles,\n",
    "        mapper,\n",
    "        reps=1,\n",
    "        initial_state=HartreeFock(\n",
    "            es_problem.num_spatial_orbitals,\n",
    "            es_problem.num_particles,\n",
    "            mapper,\n",
    "        ),\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    #SLSQP é o otimizadoer ? Testar outros, cobyla ? \n",
    "    #Pode ser qualquer otimizador mas precisamos ter cuidado pois \n",
    "    #alguns não lidam bem com o fato dos qubits not being noiseledd in real hardware\n",
    "    vqe_solver = VQE(Estimator(), ansatz, otimizador)\n",
    "    vqe_solver.initial_point = [0.0] * ansatz.num_parameters\n",
    "    \n",
    "    calc = GroundStateEigensolver(mapper, vqe_solver)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    res = calc.solve(es_problem) \n",
    "    \n",
    "    return res.groundenergy + res.nuclear_repulsion_energy "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "vamos criar uma lista de otimizadores."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "otimizadores = [SLSQP(), COBYLA(), SPSA(), NELDER_MEAD(), AQGD(), P_BFGS()]\n",
    "#QNSPSA()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "energia_by_otimizador = []\n",
    "tempos = []\n",
    "for i in otimizadores:\n",
    "    ti = time.time()\n",
    "    inf = GS_VQE(20, otimizador = i)\n",
    "    aux = [GS_VQE(a, otimizador=i) - inf for a in intervalo]\n",
    "    tf = time.time()\n",
    "    tempos.append(tf-ti)\n",
    "    energia_by_otimizador.append(aux)\n"
   ]
  },
